Vendored material (copied with local adaptations noted in each file header;
a copy of the omegacode LICENSE sits alongside the files):

  - src/executors/vendor/omegacode/  (from omegacode src/worker/, v0.0.5)
      index.ts            Worker interface, WorkerProgress, AgentError taxonomy
      types.ts            worker-facing subset of src/dsl/types.ts only —
                          AgentSpec/AgentResult/Sandbox/Effort; the workflow
                          DSL types (AgentOpts, Meta, budget) are left behind
      codex.ts            CodexWorker (codex app-server session semantics)
      codex-protocol.ts   hand-written codex app-server JSON-RPC v2 subset
      jsonrpc-stdio.ts    stdio JSON-RPC transport (framing, pending map)
      subprocess-jsonl.ts spawn-per-call JSONL subprocess mechanics
      schema.ts           JSON-Schema strictify + ajv re-validation
      errors.ts           withRetry backoff + notImplemented stub
      factory.ts          worker factory (adapted: claude-code/opencode/pi
                          branches return notImplemented; codex is the only
                          wired live provider this step)
      fake.ts             deterministic FakeWorker (the auth-free test double)
      claude.ts           vendored for adapter-family completeness but
                          EXCLUDED from compilation (tsconfig "exclude") —
                          it requires @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk, which
                          vernier does not carry yet
      opencode.ts, pi.ts  vendored, compiled, not yet wired (notImplemented)

      Local adaptations across these files: import paths from "../dsl/types.js"
      to "./types.js"; optional properties widened with `| undefined` for
      vernier's exactOptionalPropertyTypes; nothing semantic changed.

      Deliberately left behind from omegacode: src/runtime/ (the node:vm
      sandbox trunk, primitives, v3 chained call-tree resume keys, the
      determinism lint), the workflow DSL, the journal viewer/CLI, and the
      worktree module — workflow-as-untrusted-code is the trust model this
      kernel rejects, and loop-as-data makes the key lineage unnecessary.

Derived material (adapted, not copied verbatim):

  - src/ledger/ledger.ts
      journal.jsonl append/load shape, torn-line tolerance, and the
      canonical (sort-deep) JSON hashing helper are adapted from
      omegacode src/runtime/journal.ts and src/runtime/keys.ts.
      Deliberately left behind: the v3 chained call-tree key lineage
      (branch keys, fan-out counters) and the determinism lint — under
      loop-as-data the resume key collapses to hash(stepId + inputs).

  - src/kernel/types.ts
      The Executor protocol is a rename of omegacode's
      Worker.runAgent(spec, ctx) -> AgentResult seam
      (src/worker/index.ts), generalized beyond LLM providers.

  - src/executors/codex.ts
      Wraps the vendored CodexWorker behind the Executor seam; the
      AgentResult -> StepResult mapping and EffectScope -> sandbox
      derivation are vernier's.

